 Browser Support

What is an Internet Browser? 

An Internet Browser, also referred to as a user agent ua, is a software application that is used to access the internet and view web pages on your computer. What is refered to at times as “the big 5”, are some of the more common internet browsers used in Windows XP, Windows 7, Windows 8, and Windows 10 operating systems. I also added one that I like, and they are listed below.

also see: List of Web Browsers for Mac OS XFollow this link for a
List of Web Browsers for Mac OS X

There are many free browsers available. These Free Internet Browsers for Windows, are currently used by this author and are not in any particular order ?. They are as follows:

Google Chrome Updated when desired on loading

Google or just , is a freeware web browser developed by Google Inc. It is one of the best browsers for a Windows PC because of its speed, simplicity, security, privacy and customization features.

Google supports on Android 4.0 or higher, iOS 6.0or higher, Mac OSX 10.6 or higher, Windows XP SP2 or higher and Linux system.

Visit google.comhttps://www.google.com/intl/en/chrome/browser/ to learn more and download the latest version for free.

Using the test website, of the 7 browsers I tested, tied for the highest score with 521 out of 555 points. My test was ran on Friday, Feburary 17, 2016. Check out your browser with the  testhtml5test.com/.

Previous Location!
Vivaldi Updated when desired on loading

is based on Chromiums opensource platform and runs on the Blink rendering engine, the same rendering engine used by and . The interface is built in JavaScript, and Node.js, making it crossplatform and customizable. You can install Vivaldi on Windows, OS X and Linux both .deb and .rpm packages are available.

The team is commanded by former Opera Software CEO, Jon S. von Tetzchner. Hes not the only person from Opera working at this new company. It is understood that around 25 former employees are now working for , a clear sign of the disappointment some are feeling towards Opera Softwares new look at the future.

Visit vivaldi.comwww.vivaldi.com/ to learn more about the Vivaldi browser and download it for free.

Using the test website, the Vivaldi tied for the highest score with 521 out of 555 points. My test was ran on Friday, Feburary 17, 2016. Check out your browser with the  testhtml5test.com/.

is a free web browser developed by Opera Software. It works on Windows, Linux and Mac OS X. The mobile version of Opera is known as Opera Mini. Visit opera.comhttp://www.opera.com/ to learn more about the Opera Browser and download the latest version for free.

Microsoft Edge Updated via Windows Update

Microsoft Edge the new browser from microsoft is the replacement for . The default browser for Windows 10.

Developed by Microsoft, with HTMLEdge as the layout engine. It is a fork of mshtml that has removed all legacy code of older versions of and rewritten the majority of its source code with web standards and interoperability with other modern browsers in mind. Visit microsoft.comwww.microsoft.com/ Edge Details
and download to learn more and download the latest version for free.

About the Test

The test score is an indication of how well your browser supports the standard and related specifications. Find out which parts of are supported by your browser today and compare the results with other browsers.

The test does not try to test all of the new features offered by , nor does it try to test the functionality of each feature it does detect.

The score is calculated by testing for the many new features of . Each feature is worth one or more points. Apart from the main specification and other specifications created by the w3cworld wide web
consortium Working Group or web hypertext application
technology working group, this test also awards points for supporting related drafts and specifications.

Note: Please be aware that although the specification is now an official recommendation, other specifications that are being tested are still in development and could change before receiving an official status. In the future new tests will be added for new specifications and existing tests will be updated when the specifications change.

Browser Support Information:

The form element is a “Document Structure block-level Element”.

Introduced in History of an zone document. Effectively SupportedWidely Supported
elements. in most – if not all browsers.

The Google Chrome uiuser iinterface for auto-complete request varies, depending on whether autocomplete is set to off on input elements as well as their form. Specifically, when a form has autocomplete set to off and its input elements autocomplete field is not set, then if the user asks for autofill suggestions for the input element, Chrome might display a message saying: “autocomplete has been disabled for this form”.  On the other hand, if both the form and the input element have autocomplete set to off, the browser will not display that message. For this reason, you should set autocomplete to off for each input that has custom auto-completion.

Additional Information:

Gecko

Gecko, originally NGLayout is the layout engine developed by the Mozilla Project to read web content, such as , , xulxml user Interface language, JavaScript, and render it on the users screen or print it. In xulbased applications, Gecko is used to render the applications user interface as well.

Gecko is primarily used in web browsers, such as Firefox, SeaMonkey, etc. for a complete list, please refer to the Wikipedia article on Geckoen.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gecko_software#Usage that use this layout engine. It is also used in many applications, such as Mozilla’s own Thunderbird email–client application. Products using the same version of Gecko, have identical support for standards.
